    <div align="left" id="post_message_531161">I've been having a lot of fun with XCOM; at normal difficulty I seem to be stemming the tide but still getting the feeling I'm not getting an upper hand on the aliens.  My Memorial Wall is getting too big (ten soldiers after ten missions, with three of the soldiers being seven mission veterans) and I only have one soldier left from my original four (and she very nearly died on the last mission).<br />
<br />
I'm not getting enough funding to do what I want (six days away from my third council report) and France is getting ready to leave the alliance, but I've got new fighter jets being researched and hopefully if I get my satellite uplink finished I can fire a satellite up into the air to appease the French.</div>
