    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_531301">I believe that review is wrong on this count.<br />
<br />
Yes, the random number seed is created at the start of the scenario so it gets reloaded on a save game load. But it doesn't mean the exact same result happens every time. <br />
<br />
I had a floater at about 3 spaces away from a heavily wounded soldier. In 6 reloads, he shot and killed the soldier every single time with a crit.<br />
<br />
On the 7th, he missed completely. <br />
<br />
Having done a lot of save scumming, I've been looking for instances, in terms of teh RNG, a soldier is irrevocably screwed. So far, I haven't seen it. Your chances may be minimal but they're not set in stone.<br />
<br />
Now, an alien killing a soldier with a grenade may well be an inescapable fate. But that's not based on the RNG.</div>
    <!-- / message -->
    
    
